         <abstract>
            <p>A new quadrature formula for an important class of Wiener integrals is presented, in which the Wiener integrals are approximated by $n$-fold integrals with an error $O(n^{-2})$. The resulting $n$-fold integrals can then be approximated by ordinary finite sums of remarkably simple structure. An example is given.</p>
          </abstract>
